in the quality\nand quantity of the crops with ease. You can easily keep a check on the farm\nsituation and ensure production at the right pace without any hassle. &nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','How does the Remote Sensing process help us grow our food better?','','inherit','closed','closed','','5345-revision-v1','','','2019-10-16 08:45:14','2019-10-16 08:45:14','',5345,'https://iytwist.com/2019/10/16/5345-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(5348,1,'2019-10-16 09:03:34','2019-10-16 09:03:34','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>By the year 2050, the population of the World\nwill hit to 10 billion and this may increase the consumption of water, use of\nland and other resources. The resources are in the use for the rapid rising in\nthe population that competes with farming needs to provide the food. Thus,\nDigitalisation in Agriculture is helping to connect around the world regarding\nagricultural concern. Hence, Digital farming provides usage of modern\ntechnology, preservation of water, soil and energy. Although the use of modern\ntechnology will promote a rise in production and it can feed the world easily. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are a thousand types of soil, which is\nrequiring to be tested. According to the research report, It is said that\nglobal farming is expected to reach $ $23.14 billion by 2022 and it shows the\nannual growth rate of the compound by 20 % from 2017-2022. The internet of\nthings (IOTs) will promote the growth of more food on less land. Now these\ndays, satellites and drones are working as a lifeline for the farmers all\naround the world as they help them to create millions of relevant data points\nefficiently. Digitalization helps the farmer to make the right decision\nregarding applying the right fertilizer to protect the crops and selecting the\nright variety of crops.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;Digital\nfarming is all about actual time sensing, processing, and precise location (To\nmake sure that the units are collected and measured). The decision about the\ncontinuity of the farming cycle is on the quality of agriculture information\ngeneration. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is also about the endwise process,\ngeneralized operational delivery and capacity to change in the size. Providing\ninformation about the growth of crops on time when they require it. Control\nevery greenhouse variable and make gives surety about the usage of water in the\nright amount to grow healthy crops on a lesser amount.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3><strong>Why Digital Farming Needs To Be\nSuccessful?</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The benefits of technology or modern methods\nin agriculture are more than obvious. Whereas the developed countries have\nalready adopted modern technology, thus there is greed of adopting more\nscientific and technological form approaches to food production that have now\nadopted in the Asian countries and Africa. The reason behind the success of\ndigital farming is the contribution of several ingredients and the biggest\ninfrastructure. Secondly, it relies on how the medium-sized enterprises\ncontribute to the changing of farming practices effectively as possible it can.\nMost of the farmers make decisions on how to apply the fertilizers based on\nexperiments and recommendations.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Points that needs to be considered\nwhen it is right to going digital in agriculture</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Innovation in agriculture</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>ERP (Enterprise resource planning) offers a\nsolution. However, their capabilities have not customized towards innovation in\nagriculture they also offer a solution that serves agriculture. Hence, digital\nfarming doesnt only utilize the data for deciding on the cultivation process\nbut also focuses on constant learning from the data so that it can build up the\nefficiencies for the future. Good farm management software will focus on\nbuilding whatever it knows.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>To integrate with other applications is\ndifferentiated</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is to be decided where to plant the seeds\nand when to store and warehousing them.&nbsp;\nImprovements in technology have been dominance in every step of the\njourney of agri-ecosystem. To improve overall efficiency then different\napplication needs to work together with each other and must ensure the\nuninterrupted communication between the systems. To mix up with other\napplications and systems is one of the main differences while you are choosing\nfor a stable farm management.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Huge differences in farming practices</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are some features like availability of\nthe infrastructure, digital penetration and size of agricultural land depends\nupon the country to country that we travel. As there are major differences\nbetween developed and developing country\'s farming practices. Easy configurable\nsolutions leading to solve the challenges that are unique to particular\nsegments like businesses, environment, a huge difference in overcoming early\nexpectations regarding the adoption of farming practices. In such cases where\nagricultural business is said to have multi-country operations and thus, wants\nto formulate the global digital strategy on a single platform is one of the\nfactors that need to consider. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>No data loss</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Toughest challenging is while we are moving to\nmore evolving digital farming solutions or farm m